§XIL The Romans leam of Hannibal's whereabouts, and send ambassadors to demand that he be given up. The king of Pontus fears to refuse3 Hannibal's house is surrounded, and he takes poison rather than fall into the hands of his enemy.

§XIIL The exact date of his death is uncertain. The books written by and about him are numerous.
